                              <YetExpression str="The code points `/` or any |LineTerminator| occurring in the pattern shall be escaped in _S_ as necessary to ensure that the string-concatenation of *&#34;/&#34;*, _S_, *&#34;/&#34;*, and _F_ can be parsed (in an appropriate lexical context) as a |RegularExpressionLiteral| that behaves identically to the constructed regular expression. For example, if _P_ is *&#34;/&#34;*, then _S_ could be *&#34;\\/&#34;* or *&#34;\\u002F&#34;*, among other possibilities, but not *&#34;/&#34;*, because `///` followed by _F_ would be parsed as a |SingleLineComment| rather than a |RegularExpressionLiteral|. If _P_ is the empty String, this specification can be met by letting _S_ be *&#34;(?:)&#34;*." block="null"/>
